a%20Suffers%20A%20Slow%20Death%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Betwa%2C%20once%20called%20Vetravati%2C%20has%20been%20more%20than%20a%20river%20-%20it%20has%20been%20a%20song%20of%20life%2C%20a%20flowing%20hymn%20of%20history%2C%20a%20sacred%20stream%20woven%20into%20the%20cultural%20fabric%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%20Today%2C%20however%2C%20this%20river%20that%20once%20gave%20life%20to%20the%20Vindhyas%2C%20nourished%20kingdoms%2C%20and%20witnessed%20the%20footsteps%20of%20sages%20and%20warriors%20alike%2C%20lies%20in%20silence%20-%20gasping%2C%20groaning%2C%20almost%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFlowing%20from%20the%20lap%20of%20Jhiri%20village%20in%20Raisen%2C%20Betwa%20was%20known%20to%20be%20eternal%20-%20its%20waters%20a%20gift%20from%20the%20Vindhya%20ranges%2C%20flowing%20through%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20land%20all%20year%20round.%20But%20now%2C%20the%20river's%20very%20origin%20has%20dried%20up.%20What%20once%20flowed%20freely%20beneath%20ancient%20bridges%20and%20through%20sacred%20ghats%20is%20now%20barren%20soil%2C%20cracked%20and%20thirsty%2C%20carrying%20the%20stench%20of%20neglect%20and%20greed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBetwa%20has%20been%20flowing%20since%20the%20Vedic%20times.%20There%20was%20a%20stepwell%20at%20its%20origin.%20Now%2C%20that%20too%20has%20dried%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20lamented%20Gopal%20Das%20Maharaj%2C%20a%20custodian%20of%20the%20river's%20legacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Vedas%2C%20Betwa%20was%20sung%20about%20in%20verses.%20In%20the%20Mahabharata%2C%20she%20was%20revered%20as%20Vetravati%20-%20a%20river%20of%20penance%2C%20purity%2C%20and%20perseverance.%20Today%2C%20the%20same%20river%20is%20encircled%20by%20cement%2C%20her%20veins%20punctured%20by%20illegal%20borings%2C%20her%20lifeblood%20stolen%20by%20endless%20greed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%20her%20birthplace%2C%20a%20cement%20wall%20now%20imprisons%20her%20spirit%2C%20while%20illegal%20deforestation%20and%20sand%20mining%20ravage%20her%20body.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20river's%20natural%20sources%2C%20once%20replenished%20by%20the%20monsoons%20and%20Vindhya's%20embrace%2C%20have%20withered.%20The%20sounds%20of%20her%20flow%20have%20been%20replaced%20by%20silence%2C%20broken%20only%20by%20the%20hum%20of%20machines%20boring%20into%20her%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20Raisen%20to%20Vidisha%2C%20Betwa's%20waters%20are%20being%20siphoned%20off%20through%20borings.%20The%20forests%20that%20protected%20her%20have%20been%20cut%2C%20and%20her%20natural%20flow%20blocked.%20This%20is%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20kill%20Betwa%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rakesh%20Meena%2C%20an%20environmentalist%20whose%20voice%20trembles%20with%20both%20anger%20and%20grief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20just%20nature's%20fury%20-%20it%20is%20human%20folly.%20It%20is%20the%20result%20of%20unchecked%20construction%2C%20mindless%20excavation%2C%20and%20complete%20apathy.%20The%20catchment%20areas%20that%20once%20stored%20water%20for%20dry%20months%20have%20been%20consumed%20by%20concrete.%20Villages%20and%20fields%20that%20once%20thrived%20by%20her%20side%20now%20watch%20helplessly%20as%20their%20lifeline%20disappears.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBetwa%20is%20fighting%20for%20her%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Brijendra%20Pandey%2C%20a%20social%20worker.%20%26quot%3BForty%20years%20ago%2C%20we%20protested%20when%20Bhopal's%20dirty%20water%20was%20dumped%20into%20her.%20We%20appealed%20to%20leaders%2C%20to%20authorities%2C%20but%20no%20one%20listened.%20Today%2C%20she%20lies%20dying%2C%20and%20still%2C%20no%20one%20cares.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarmers%2C%20too%2C%20are%20witnessing%20the%20slow%20death%20of%20their%20river.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%26quot%3BThe%20water%20flow%20is%20completely%20broken.%20The%20river%20has%20been%20abandoned%2C%20just%20like%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Laxman%20Meena%20is%20a%20farmer%20whose%20fields%20now%20wait%20for%20rains%20that%20may%20never%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20little%2