0were%20pertinent%20to%20the%20current%20electronic%20and%20social%20media%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20issues%20raised%20in%20the%20plea%20were%20quite%20serious%2C%20considering%20the%20contemporary%20times%20of%20an%20electronic%20era%20and%20social%20media.%20Prima%20facie%2C%20it%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20commercial%20exploitation%20of%20the%20petitioner's%20photograph%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20High%20Court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20alleged%20to%20have%20happened%20completely%20without%20the%20woman%20even%20being%20informed%20about%20the%20same%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20issued%20a%20notice%20to%20Shutterstock%2C%20a%20US-based%20company%20that%20hosts%20a%20website%20with%20royalty-free%20stock%20photographs%2C%20and%20various%20state%20governments%2C%20including%20Maharashtra%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20Telangana%20and%20Odisha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20notice%20was%20also%20issued%20to%20the%20Telangana%20Congress%2C%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Rural%20Development%2C%20and%20a%20private%20entity%2C%20Total%20Dental%20Care%20Pvt%20Ltd%2C%20which%20had%20used%20the%20petitioner's%20photograph.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20sought%20affidavits%20from%20all%20the%20respondents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20High%20Court%20said%20the%20present%20case%20brings%20to%20the%20fore%20a%20serious%20issue%20about%20the%20unauthorised%20use%20of%20woman's%20photograph%20by%20various%20political%20parties%20and%20state%20governments%20in%20advertising%20their%20schemes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20woman%20in%20her%20plea%20termed%20as%20extremely%20alarming%20such%20a%20breach%20of%20her%20privacy%20and%20illegality%20which%20ought%20not%20to%20have%20taken%20place%20from%20responsible%20governments%20who%20are%20supposed%20to%20adhere%20to%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20woman%2C%20one%20Tukaram%20Karve%2C%20a%20photographer%20from%20her%20village%2C%20had%20taken%20her%20picture%20and%20uploaded%20it%20without%20her%20consent%20on%20the%20Shutterstock%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20governments%20of%20Maharashtra%2C%20Telangana%2C%20Odisha%20and%20Karnataka%2C%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Rural%20Development%20and%20some%20private%20entities%20have%20used%20her%20photograph%20from%20the%20website%20without%20her%20consent%20for%20their%20advertisements%20and%20hoardings%2C%20she%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20woman%20further%20said%20that%20the%20government's%20illegal%20use%20of%20her%20photograph%20was%20a%20breach%20of%20her%20fundamental%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20sought%20a%20direction%20to%20the%20respondents%20to%20be%20permanently%20restrained%20from%20using%20her%20photograph%20on%20their%20websites%2C%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20advertisements%20and%20promotions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742218920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Frmvo6quo_bombay-high-court_625x300_27_September_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbombay-high-court-on-use-of-womans-pic-in-government-ads-commercial-exploitation-7943233%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Bombay%20High%20Court%20has%20termed%20the%20use%20of%20a%20woman's%20image%20without%20her%20consent%20in%20government%20advertisements%20as%20%26quot%3Bcommercial%20exploitation%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bquite%20serious%26quot%3B%20considering%20the%20contemporary%20electronic%20era%20and%20social%20media.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Not%20just%20Trump%3A%20Why%20crushing%20free%20speech%20is%20a%20feature%20of%20American%20democracy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742218442000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%