%20as%20the%20festival%20of%20colours%2C%20was%20celebrated%20on%20Friday%2C%20two%20days%20before%20Ms%20Gabbard%2C%20who%20follows%20Hindu%20tradition%2C%20arrived%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20what%20Holi%20means%20to%20her%2C%20she%20said%20it%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bwonderful%20and%20colourful%26quot%3B%20celebration%20of%20life%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bconnection%20that%20we%20all%20share%20as%20people%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20something%20from%20my%20home%20in%20Hawaii%2C%20where%20we%20greet%20each%20other%20with%20'Aloha'.%20Here%20in%20India%2C%20we%20greet%20each%20other%20with%20'Namaste'.%20But%20the%20deeper%20spiritual%20meaning%20of%20these%20two%20words%20is%20the%20same%20in%20recognizing%20the%20eternal%20and%20divine%20spirit%20that%20exists%20within%20all%20of%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20at%20a%20personal%20level%2C%20this%20is%20very%2C%20very%20meaningful%20and%20also%20very%20practical%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fis-newly-appointed-dni-tulsi-gabbard-of-indian-origin-her-hindu-name-sparks-curiosity-7715093%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETulsi%20Gabbard%3C%2Fa%3E's%20mother%2C%20born%20on%20the%20US%20mainland%2C%20had%20embraced%20Hinduism%20and%20raised%20her%20in%20the%20tradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Gabbard's%20first%20name%2C%20Tulsi%2C%20is%20a%20sacred%20plant%20in%20Hinduism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2043-year-old%20was%20the%20first%20Hindu%20American%20elected%20to%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives.%20She%20swore%20her%20oath%20to%20enter%20Congress%20on%20the%20Hindu%20scripture%2C%20Bhagavad%20Gita.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Gabbard%20also%20got%20married%20in%20a%20Hindu%20ceremony%20to%20a%20Hawaii-based%20cinematographer%2C%20Abraham%20Williams.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20she%20was%20appointed%20as%20the%20Director%20of%20National%20Intelligence%20(D